chapters:
If a person does not repent,
    God will sharpen his sword;
    he will bend and string his bow.

The wicked conceive evil;
    they are pregnant with trouble
    and give birth to lies.

But in my distress I cried out to the Lord;
    yes, I prayed to my God for help.
He heard me from his sanctuary;
    my cry to him reached his ears.

Then the earth quaked and trembled.
    The foundations of the mountains shook;
    they quaked because of his anger.

Smoke poured from his nostrils;
    fierce flames leaped from his mouth.
    Glowing coals blazed forth from him.

The Lord thundered from heaven;
    the voice of the Most High resounded
    amid the hail and burning coals.

You have given me your shield of victory.
    Your right hand supports me;
    your help has made me great.

You gave me victory over my accusers.
    You appointed me ruler over nations;
    people I don’t even know now serve me.

and rescues me from my enemies.
You hold me safe beyond the reach of my enemies;
    you save me from violent opponents.

You give great victories to your king;
    you show unfailing love to your anointed,
    to David and all his descendants forever.

Do not stay so far from me,
    for trouble is near,
    and no one else can help me.

My enemies surround me like a pack of dogs;
    an evil gang closes in on me.
    They have pierced my hands and feet.

Who is the King of glory?
    The Lord, strong and mighty;
    the Lord, invincible in battle.

Declare me innocent, O Lord,
    for I have acted with integrity;
    I have trusted in the Lord without wavering.

For he will conceal me there when troubles come;
    he will hide me in his sanctuary.
    He will place me out of reach on a high rock.

Do not let me fall into their hands.
    For they accuse me of things I’ve never done;
    with every breath they threaten me with violence.

O Lord, I have come to you for protection;
    don’t let me be disgraced.
    Save me, for you do what is right.

I will be glad and rejoice in your unfailing love,
    for you have seen my troubles,
    and you care about the anguish of my soul.

I am dying from grief;
    my years are shortened by sadness.
Sin has drained my strength;
    I am wasting away from within.

For you are my hiding place;
    you protect me from trouble.
    You surround me with songs of victory. Interlude

But they are glad now that I am in trouble;
    they gleefully join together against me.
I am attacked by people I don’t even know;
    they slander me constantly.

You have made my life no longer than the width of my hand.
    My entire lifetime is just a moment to you;
    at best, each of us is but a breath.” Interlude

Day and night I have only tears for food,
    while my enemies continually taunt me, saying,
    “Where is this God of yours?”

He causes wars to end throughout the earth.
    He breaks the bow and snaps the spear;
    he burns the shields with fire.

Oh, give me back my joy again;
    you have broken me—
    now let me rejoice.

All day long you plot destruction.
    Your tongue cuts like a sharp razor;
    you’re an expert at telling lies.

For strangers are attacking me;
    violent people are trying to kill me.
    They care nothing for God. Interlude

I will sacrifice a voluntary offering to you;
    I will praise your name, O Lord,
    for it is good.

Let death stalk my enemies;
    let the grave swallow them alive,
    for evil makes its home within them.

He ransoms me and keeps me safe
    from the battle waged against me,
    though many still oppose me.

My heart is confident in you, O God;
    my heart is confident.
    No wonder I can sing your praises!

Then at last everyone will say,
    “There truly is a reward for those who live for God;
    surely there is a God who judges justly here on earth.”

Listen to the filth that comes from their mouths;
    their words cut like swords.
    “After all, who can hear us?” they sneer.

Don’t kill them, for my people soon forget such lessons;
    stagger them with your power, and bring them to their knees,
    O Lord our shield.

O my Strength, to you I sing praises,
    for you, O God, are my refuge,
    the God who shows me unfailing love.

God has spoken plainly,
    and I have heard it many times:
Power, O God, belongs to you;

O God, you are my God;
    I earnestly search for you.
My soul thirsts for you;
    my whole body longs for you
in this parched and weary land
    where there is no water.

Then everyone will be afraid;
    they will proclaim the mighty acts of God
    and realize all the amazing things he does.

Everything on earth will worship you;
    they will sing your praises,
    shouting your name in glorious songs.” Interlude

For by his great power he rules forever.
    He watches every movement of the nations;
    let no rebel rise in defiance. Interlude

God places the lonely in families;
    he sets the prisoners free and gives them joy.
But he makes the rebellious live in a sun-scorched land.

Tell everyone about God’s power.
    His majesty shines down on Israel;
    his strength is mighty in the heavens.

But as for me, I am poor and needy;
    please hurry to my aid, O God.
You are my helper and my savior;
    O Lord, do not delay.

Yes, you have been with me from birth;
    from my mother’s womb you have cared for me.
    No wonder I am always praising you!

My health may fail, and my spirit may grow weak,
    but God remains the strength of my heart;
    he is mine forever.

The clouds poured down rain;
    the thunder rumbled in the sky.
    Your arrows of lightning flashed.

Your thunder roared from the whirlwind;
    the lightning lit up the world!
    The earth trembled and shook.

He turned his anger against them;
    he did not spare the Egyptians’ lives
    but ravaged them with the plague.

He drove out the nations before them;
    he gave them their inheritance by lot.
    He settled the tribes of Israel into their homes.

You cried to me in trouble, and I saved you;
    I answered out of the thundercloud
    and tested your faith when there was no water at Meribah. Interlude

All the nations you made
    will come and bow before you, Lord;
    they will praise your holy name.

O God, insolent people rise up against me;
    a violent gang is trying to kill me.
    You mean nothing to them.

Look down and have mercy on me.
    Give your strength to your servant;
    save me, the son of your servant.

My eyes are blinded by my tears.
Each day I beg for your help, O Lord;
    I lift my hands to you for mercy.

This I declare about the Lord:
He alone is my refuge, my place of safety;
    he is my God, and I trust him.

When they call on me, I will answer;
    I will be with them in trouble.
    I will rescue and honor them.

The floods have risen up, O Lord.
    The floods have roared like thunder;
    the floods have lifted their pounding waves.

Enter his gates with thanksgiving;
    go into his courts with praise.
    Give thanks to him and praise his name.

you lay out the rafters of your home in the rain clouds.
You make the clouds your chariot;
    you ride upon the wings of the wind.

Let me share in the prosperity of your chosen ones.
    Let me rejoice in the joy of your people;
    let me praise you with those who are your heritage.

Because of this, the earth opened up;
    it swallowed Dathan
    and buried Abiram and the other rebels.

For he has gathered the exiles from many lands,
    from east and west,
    from north and south.

Their ships were tossed to the heavens
    and plunged again to the depths;
    the sailors cringed in terror.

For he refused all kindness to others;
    he persecuted the poor and needy,
    and he hounded the brokenhearted to death.

He loved to curse others;
    now you curse him.
He never blessed others;
    now don’t you bless him.

He will punish the nations
    and fill their lands with corpses;
    he will shatter heads over the whole earth.

The wicked will see this and be infuriated.
    They will grind their teeth in anger;
    they will slink away, their hopes thwarted.

Death wrapped its ropes around me;
    the terrors of the grave overtook me.
    I saw only trouble and sorrow.

O Lord, I am your servant;
    yes, I am your servant, born into your household;
    you have freed me from my chains.

For his unfailing love for us is powerful;
    the Lord’s faithfulness endures forever.
Praise the Lord!

They swarmed around me like bees;
    they blazed against me like a crackling fire.
    But I destroyed them all with the authority of the Lord.

I have wandered away like a lost sheep;
    come and find me,
    for I have not forgotten your commands.

It is useless for you to work so hard
    from early morning until late at night,
anxiously working for food to eat;
    for God gives rest to his loved ones.

I am counting on the Lord;
    yes, I am counting on him.
    I have put my hope in his word.

O Israel, hope in the Lord;
    for with the Lord there is unfailing love.
    His redemption overflows.

May my tongue stick to the roof of my mouth
    if I fail to remember you,
    if I don’t make Jerusalem my greatest joy.

The proud have set a trap to catch me;
    they have stretched out a net;
    they have placed traps all along the way. Interlude

Hear my prayer, O Lord;
    listen to my plea!
    Answer me because you are faithful and righteous.

Reach down from heaven and rescue me;
    rescue me from deep waters,
    from the power of my enemies.

He has not done this for any other nation;
    they do not know his regulations.
Praise the Lord!

Let them all praise the name of the Lord.
    For his name is very great;
    his glory towers over the earth and heaven!

Praise the Lord!
Praise God in his sanctuary;
    praise him in his mighty heaven!
